ough an OpenSpec change.\\n+\\n+## 6. Identity and ownership\\n+\\n+Authenticated identity comes from the server-validated opaque session. Client\\n+parameters, request bodies, query strings, and model arguments never select the\\n+acting user or tenant scope.\\n+\\n+### 6.1 Organizational units\\n+\\n+Nested organizational units, memberships, inherited roles, external identities,\\n+and their datastore invariants ship as identity foundations. Their current\\n+contracts live in [`openspec/specs/org-units`](openspec/specs/org-units/spec.md),\\n+[`openspec/specs/org-memberships`](openspec/specs/org-memberships/spec.md), and\\n+[`openspec/specs/external-identities`](openspec/specs/external-identities/spec.md).\\n+\\n+## 7. Authorization and roles\\n+\\n+Authorization fails closed. Tenant-owned tables use PostgreSQL row-level security\\n+with `ENABLE` and `FORCE`; application queries run with a transaction-local\\n+trusted user id. Missing identity must not widen access.\\n+\\n+### 7.1 External identities\\n+\\n+External identity mappings bind a provider subject to one llame user. They are an\\n+identity primitive, not a channel permission grant.\\n+\\n+### 7.2 Organizational access\\n+\\n+Org-unit access and inheritance follow the current OpenSpec capability contracts.\\n+They do not imply shared access to Projects, Chats, tools, or future knowledge.\\n+\\n+### 7.3 Roles\\n+\\n+Current organizational roles are `owner`, `admin`, `maintainer`, `member`,\\n+`viewer`, `guest`, and `service_account`. Capability-specific authorization must\\n+still be explicit.\\n+\\n+### 7.5 Approvals\\n+\\n+No general approval workflow or per-tool allow/ask/deny policy ships. Existing\\n+authentication, RLS, tool safety classification, and the static operator\\n+`tools.allowed` gate remain mandatory.\\n+\\n+## 9. Chats and durable Runs\\n+\\n+A Chat is the persistent conversation container. A Run is one queued agentic\\n+turn for a user message.\\n+\\n+### 9.4 Run events\\n+\\n+Run progress is an append-only event stream. Clients subscribe, reconnect, and\\n+replay; they do not own execution state. Tool activity and terminal outcomes are\\n+persisted for history reconstruction.\\n+\\n+### 9.5 Execution boundary\\n+\\n+Every chat message executes through pg-boss and the transport-agnostic\\n+`RunExecutionService`. There is no inline request-thread execution mode. A\\n+dedicated no-HTTP worker entrypoint ships, and the same worker profiles also\\n+support co-located consumers. See\\n+[`openspec/specs/durable-runs`](openspec/specs/durable-runs/spec.md),\\n+[`openspec/specs/job-queue`](openspec/specs/job-queue/spec.md), and\\n+[docs/scaling.md](docs/scaling.md).\\n+\\n+## 13. Tools and integrations\\n+\\n+The current Run loop can interleave model output with tool calls and observations\\n+within an operator step cap. The only shipped native tool is\\n+`search_conversations`. Remote MCP and dynamic tool discovery do not ship yet.\\n+\\n+### 13.5 Tool safety classification\\n+\\n+Every registered tool declares one classification: `read_only`,\\n+`write_low_risk`, `write_high_risk`, `execute_code`, `external_send`,\\n+`financial_or_sensitive`, or `admin`. The current runtime advertises and executes\\n+only operator-allowlisted `read_only` tools. See\\n+[`openspec/specs/tool-calling`](openspec/specs/tool-calling/spec.md).\\n+\\n+## 14. Provider and model configuration\\n+\\n+Instance operators configure providers, models, defaults, and secret references\\n+through `llame.config.json`. The API exposes only executable model metadata and\\n+routes the selected opaque model id through the Run. User-owned provider\\n+credentials and BYOK do not ship. See\\n+[`openspec/specs/instance-config`](openspec/specs/instance-config/spec.md) and\\n+[`openspec/specs/available-models`](openspec/specs/available-models/spec.md).\\n+\\n+## 15. Knowledge\\n+\\n+No Markdown vault, Knowledge Space, knowledge index, or agent knowledge-write\\n+path ships. Chat search is not a knowledge base. The next committed boundary is\\n+defined by [ROADMAP.md](ROADMAP.md), not by an illustrative schema here.\\n+\\n+## 19. Channels\\n+\\n+No external messaging channel ships.\\n+\\n+### 19.2 External identity mapping\\n+\\n+The provider-subject mapping in §7.1 is reusable by future channels, but a mapping\\n+alone does not authorize message delivery or resource access.\\n+\\n+## 20. Memory and search\\n+\\n+Chats, Runs, messages, and events form the current episodic record. Hybrid chat\\n+search is a derived, rebuildable projection and is available through the web UI\\n+and `search_conversations`. Semantic facts and automatic memory injection do not\\n+ship. See [`openspec/specs/chat-search`](openspec/specs/chat-search/spec.md) and\\n+[`openspec/specs/search-projection`](openspec/specs/search-projection/spec.md).\\n+\\n+## 22. Service ownership\\n+\\n+### 22.0 Web and API boundary\\n+\\n+`apps/api` owns HTTP APIs, authentication, execution services, and the database.\\n+It is the only application that reads or writes PostgreSQL.\\n+\\n+`apps/web` is a thin Next.js client. It has no database connection, chat backend,\\n+or BFF-owned domain state. It consumes `apps/api` through the documented HTTP and\\n+streaming contracts.\\n+\\n+## 23. Technology constraints\\n+\\n+### 23.1 Runtime stack\\n+\\n+The product is TypeScript end to end on Node.js: Next.js in `apps/web`, NestJS in\\n+`apps/api`, Drizzle for database access, and pg-boss for queued work. Do not add a\\n+second backend language or a parallel execution path without an explicit\\n+architecture decision.\\n+\\n+## 24. Storage and coordination\\n+\\n+### 24.0.1 PostgreSQL coordination\\n+\\n+PostgreSQL is the current system of record for operational state and the shared\\n+coordination substrate for transactions, RLS, queues, locks, sessions, events,\\n+and lexical search. Derived search projections may be rebuilt; authoritative\\n+identity, Run, and audit state may not be reconstructed from prompts or